27 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code 9-15-208 is amended to read as follows:
28 9-15-208. Law enforcement assistance.
29 (a) When an order of protection is issued under this chapter, upon
30 request of the petitioner the circuit court may order a law enforcement
31 officer with jurisdiction to accompany the petitioner and assist in placing
32 the petitioner in possession of the dwelling or residence or to otherwise
33 assist in execution or service of the order of protection.
34 (b) The court may also order a law enforcement officer to assist the
35 petitioner in returning to the residence and getting personal effects.
36 (c) If law enforcement is assisting in the execution or service of an
